# Cursor Rules — GDGC Hackathon 2026

Mode: HACKATHON. Speed over perfection.

Stack: Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui, Gemini API, Supabase.

## Hard rules

- No `any` — use typed alternatives
- shadcn/ui components only — no custom UI primitives
- Tailwind v4 utility classes — no inline styles
- No refactoring untouched code
- No tests unless explicitly asked
- Keep components under 200 lines — extract if larger
- Keep functions under 50 lines

## Layer ownership

Only write code in your assigned area. Ask before touching another owner's path.

| Area | Owner | Path |
|------|-------|------|
| AI / Gemini + Supabase + Vercel | Ray | `src/lib/` |
| Backend / API routes | Aryan | `src/app/api/` |
| Frontend / UI | Hemish | `src/components/` |
| Pages | Maalav | `src/app/` (non-API) |
| Types | All | `src/types/` |

## Commits

`feat: add x` / `fix: handle y` / `chore: install z`
Imperative, lowercase, no period, ASCII only.

## Demo-path-first

Every piece of code must connect to the demo. If it is not demoable in 4 minutes, cut it.

## Fallbacks

`src/lib/fallbacks.ts` has mock data for all external services.
`USE_FALLBACKS=true` in `.env.local` activates them.
